This paper discusses the problem of searching in distributed machine learning models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a quality metric to forward search requests, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of entropy-based metrics could also relate to data structures (cs.DS). The paper discusses the benefits of distributed learning, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of data from a specific location, which could relate to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
